Uses of Interface
pqueue.heaps.MinHeap

  • Packages that use MinHeap 
    Package Description
    pqueue.heaps  

    • Uses of MinHeap in pqueue.heaps

      Classes in pqueue.heaps that implement MinHeap 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  ArrayMinHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
      ArrayMinHeap is a MinHeap implemented using an internal array.
      class  LinkedMinHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
      A LinkedMinHeap is a tree (specifically, a complete binary tree) where every node is smaller than or equal to its descendants (as defined by the Comparable.compareTo(Object) overridings of the type T).
      Constructors in pqueue.heaps with parameters of type MinHeap 
      Constructor and Description
      ArrayMinHeap(MinHeap<T> other)
      Copy constructor initializes this as a carbon copy of the MinHeap parameter.
      LinkedMinHeap(MinHeap<T> other)
      Copy constructor initializes this as a carbon copy of the parameter, which is of the general type MinHeap! Since MinHeap is an Iterable type, we can access all of its elements in proper order and insert them into this.
